CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 19, 1953, pg. 6 reads: "Elk Honorees - Iron City Elks Lodge celebrated its fifty-second anniversary last week by honoring three local citizens at a banquet. The honorees were, left to right: Dr. Alma Illery, founder and president of the National Achievement Clubs, Inc.; William pg. Young, Republican candidate for City Council and a welfare director for the Lockhart Steel Company, and Carl Dickerson, of the Duquesne Elks Lodge.  Messrs. Dickerson and Young were honored as Elks' "Man of the Year" and "Mr. Elk," respectively. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Unknown man, William P. Young, and Carl Dickerson wearing Elks chain collar gathered at banquet for Iron City Elks Lodge fifty-second anniversary
